{"key":"processedPost-9980781","value":{"id":9980781,"first":9980308,"last":10029673,"when":1237215395,"utime":"03/16/09 05:56 PM","content":"I've grown mushrooms outdoors in Alaska, and also in WA State.&nbsp; They'll do fine in NY.&nbsp; Put them where they get some morning sun, and afternoon shade.&nbsp; Spawn cakes to manure in a 4\" deep bed, and cover with a small amount of topsoil.&nbsp; Only water when necessary to keep the bed from completely drying out.&nbsp; They'll fruit when you get a week of rain, or in late summer you can trigger a fruiting by turning on a sprinkler every few hours for only a few minutes at a time to keep the humidity at the surface high.&nbsp; This will simulate rain.&nbsp; Plant grass seed over the bed too, as the grass will hold high humidity at the surface where they pin.<br />RR","title":"Re: Outdoor Cultivation, Upstate NY?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}